In this article, President Trump addresses the upcoming Senate vote on legislation to replace Obamacare. He highlights the negative impact of Obamacare on American lives and shares the story of a family whose health insurance premiums skyrocketed under the law. Trump criticizes the promises made by Democrat politicians who passed Obamacare, claiming they were lies. He emphasizes that the Senate health care bill will stop the Obamacare disaster, expand choice, and drive down costs. Trump mentions that the bill will reduce premiums, allow states to create innovative health care solutions, provide funding for people with expensive health conditions, double the amount that Americans can contribute to Health Savings Accounts, and give states more flexibility in managing their Medicaid programs. He concludes by stating that the legislation is close to ending the healthcare nightmare and will provide affordable and quality healthcare.